      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>This handful of matte, multicolored crystals looks like a pile of smoothed sea glass. As a standard action, you can throw these tiny crystals into the air to surround you and form a blazing array of colorful, magical light. Until the beginning of your next turn, your body sheds bright light in a 30-foot radius and you gain @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Kjba2E3Ad5oMJ7hV.JournalEntryPage.nyB6pt2dd6iVQGmS]{concealment}.</p>\n<p>Any creature that ends its turn adjacent to you while your fireworks crystals are active must succeed at a DC 13 Fortitude save or be @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.Item.tOpF6qjnlnKc10t7]{blinded} for 1 round. Once used, the crystals become inert.</p>"
